This guide will help you launch any of the three tactical simulators (Pacific War 1, Tankgaem.py, or Navalgaem) on your specific device. All games require Python 3 to run locally.

💻 PC (Windows & Linux)
Install Python: Download and install the latest version from python.org. Ensure you check the box that says "Add Python to PATH" during installation.

Download the Files: Place PacificWar1.py, Tankgaem.py, and navalgaem in a dedicated folder.

Open Terminal/CMD: * On Windows, press Win + R, type cmd, and hit Enter.

On Linux, open your preferred Terminal.

Navigate & Run: Use the cd command to enter your game folder and type:

python Tankgaem.py


python navalgaem 

🍎 Mac (macOS)
Check Python: Most Macs come with Python, but you should install the latest version via python.org or Homebrew (brew install python).

Open Terminal: Press Cmd + Space, type "Terminal," and hit Enter.

Run with Python3: macOS often requires the python3 command specifically:

python3 Tankgaem.py


python3 navalgaem 

🍓 Raspberry Pi (Raspbian/OS)
Pre-installed: Python 3 is installed by default on Raspberry Pi OS.

Access Terminal: Click the terminal icon in the top taskbar.

Execute: Navigate to your folder and run:

python3 Tankgaem.py


python3 navalgaem 

Note: These games are lightweight and run perfectly on all Pi models.

💻 Chromebook
There are two ways to play on a Chromebook:

The Easy Way (No Setup)
Go to online-python.com.

Drag and Drop the .py file (e.g., Tankgaem.py) directly onto the editor window.

Click the "Run" button.

The Pro Way (Linux Environment)
Go to Settings > Advanced > Developers and turn on Linux development environment (Beta).

Open the Terminal app from your launcher.

Update your packages: sudo apt-get update.

Move your game files into the "Linux files" folder in your Files app.

Run: python3 Tankgaem.py or python3 navalgaem.
